<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 8:07AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...AREAS OF FOG THIS MORNING in Jim Hogg and Brooks Counties...
Current observations are indicating fog reducing visibilities to
between one half mile and 1 mile, with isolated pockets of denser
fog reducing the visibility to around one quarter-mile. The fog
is expected to lift between 9AM and 10AM CDT this morning.
Use caution during the morning commute, as visibility may change
rapidly in a short amount of time. Use low beam headlights and
leave extra distance between your vehicle and others on the road.</description>
